          "type": "text",
          "text": "Perfect! Your 7-segment counter is ready. Here's the wiring summary:\n\n**Wiring Table:**\n| Segment | Arduino Pin | Series Resistor |\n|---------|-------------|-----------------|\n| a       | D2          | 220Ω           |\n| b       | D3          | 220Ω           |\n| c       | D4          | 220Ω           |\n| d       | D5          | 220Ω           |\n| e       | D6          | 220Ω           |\n| f       | D7          | 220Ω           |\n| g       | D8          | 220Ω           |\n| gnd     | GND         | —              |\n| Button  | D9          | (INPUT_PULLUP) |\n\n**How it works:**\n- Press the button to increment the counter from 0–9, then it wraps back to 0.\n- The sketch uses debouncing (20ms) to prevent false triggers.\n- Each segment is driven through a 220Ω current-limiting resistor (~16mA per segment at 5V).\n- Button uses `INPUT_PULLUP` with active-LOW detection (pulls to GND when pressed).\n\nThe circuit is safe—each pin draws <20mA, well within Arduino limits."
        }
      ]
    }
